   [5] <a href="javascript:card_browser(228)">The Bridge of Khazad-dum</a><br>
   [6] Valley of the Silverlode<br>
   [7] <a href="javascript:card_browser(233)">Anduin Wilderland</a><br>
   [8] <a href="javascript:card_browser(238)">Shores of Nen Hithoel</a><br>
   [9] <a href="javascript:card_browser(242)">Summit of Amon Hen</a><br>
<br>
Free Peoples (41 + 3 starting)<br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(168)">Bilbo Baggins, Retired Adventurer</a><br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(170)">Bounder</a><br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(172)">Farmer Maggot, Chaser of Rascals</a><br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(885)">The Gaffer, Sam&#39;s Father</a> x 2<br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(873)">Hobbit Party Guest</a> x 3<br>
   Master Proudfoot, Distant Relatve of Bilbo x 3<br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(875)">Rosie Cotton, Hobbiton Lass</a><br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(180)">Hobbit Sword</a> x 3<br>
   Mithril-Coat<br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(194)">Sting</a><br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(198)">Thror&#39;s Map</a><br>
   O Elbereth! Gilthoniel! x 2<br>
   A Promise x 4<br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(196)">A Talent for Not Being Seen</a><br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(197)">There and Back Again</a> x 4<br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(178)">Hobbit Intuition</a> x 4<br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(179)">Hobbit Stealth</a> x 4<br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(190)">Power According to His Stature</a> x 4<br>
   <br>
Shadow (44)<br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(58)">Ancient Chieftain</a><br>
   The Balrog, Flame of Udun<br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(312)">Cave Troll of Moria, Scourge of the Black Pit</a> x 3<br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(68)">Goblin Backstabber</a> x 4<br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(72)">Goblin Runner</a> x 4<br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(73)">Goblin Scavengers</a> x 4<br>
   Goblin Scrabbler x 2<br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(81)">Guard Commander</a><br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(86)">Moria Scout</a> x 4<br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(94)">Troll&#39;s Keyward</a> x 2<br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(313)">Cave Troll&#39;s Hammer</a><br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(75)">Goblin Scimitar</a> x 4<br>
   Goblin <a href="javascript:card_browser(303)">Armor</a>y x 4<br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(78)">Goblin Swarms</a> x 2<br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(91)">They Are Coming</a> x 3<br>
   <a href="javascript:card_browser(82)">Host of Thousands</a> x 4<br>
       </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> OK, first off, I know the deck looks large.  But with the &quot;drawing&quot; of Proudfoot, and the discarding of They Are Coming, it gets small in a hurry.  I rarely have more than 10 cards left upon victory.<br>
<br>
Starting Fellowship-<br>
  Hobbits sure are a crafty bunch!  Frodo, Old Bilbo&#39;s Heir is the best Frodo for this deck, as healing Gaffer, Bilbo, and even Bounder can be a huge advantage, much more than a -1 to his possesions and tales.  This is not a choke style hobbit deck, so 1 twilight isn&#39;t so big.  The Isildur&#39;s Bane is a lifesaver against the archery of Orc Bowmen, and the Moria Archery deck is getting more popular (and powerful) all of the time.  Merry, Horticulturalist is one of the toughest choices I had to make for the deck.  By using him over the rare Merry I accomplished a few things.  It starts my hobbit healing engine, thins my deck, and when I wait until site 3 to do it, draws me a card.  And the wound is immediatly healed by Maggot!  Pippen, Hobbit of Some Intelligence allows you to bid 1 more, as he heals it immediatly.  Sam, Son of Hamfast allows you to bid 4 more, get your site 1, pull his dad and heal!<br>
<br>
Adventure Path-<br>
1. Bag End - Exert Pippin to get The Gaffer, heal Sam, remove another burden from Frodo.  Allows you to go first by bidding high, and many times denying your opponent Aragorn or Sam, which makes it easier to swarm.<br>
<br>
2. Buckleberry Ferry - Only gives up 1 twilight, and no battles!<br>
<br>
3. Frodo&#39;s Bedroom - With 12 hobbit ally cards in the deck, lets you get cards back.  Also, holding off to play Maggot here nets you a card!<br>
<br>
4. Moria Stairway - Only gives 2 twilight, and you have 4 swords for your hobbits, and 4 swords for your orcs. Cave Troll with Hammer is damage 4!<br>
<br>
5. The Bridge of Khazad-dum - No choice here, but home of the Balrog = wounds a plenty. Perfect place to stealth.<br>
<br>
6. Valley of the Silverlode - Hobbits recover from Balrog, and heal upon arrival.<br>
<br>
7. Anduin Wilderland - You have no archery on either side, so it can&#39;t hurt.  Nice vs. Rangers, Orc Bowmen, and other random archers.<br>
<br>
8. Shores of Nen Hithoel - Stop sign.  Enough said.<br>
<br>
9. Summit of Amon Hen - If they pass you, and have burdens, the 8 twilight plus card drawing should do them in!<br>
<br>
Fellowship Deck - <br>
  One copy of Bilbo has proven to be enough, as he is best at the end, making sure your PATHS and tales make it back in for the run. One Bounder is also plenty, as rarely should you need him.  Farmer Maggot gets found by Merry, and The Gaffer is so important I run 2, in case you don&#39;t start.  Hobbit Party Guests keep the healing going.  Master Proudfoot is maybe the most important ally in the deck.  Using him twice at the beginning of your fellowship should get you 3 cards, and more (but remember the rule of 4)if you can Sting and use him again!  Rosie Cotton helps healing and burden removal, along with boosting Sam.  Three hobbit swords help keep your posse from being overwhelmed.  Mithril-coat is nice against alomost any deck, whether it be archery, weapons, or damage bonuses.  Sting makes Proudfoot better, and helps you survive orcs.  Thror&#39;s Map is the card I would like to fit one more of in this deck.  Your path is the ideal one, and with so many hobbits, the wounds are not so bad.  O Elbereth is important against Nazgul, and a nice bonus overall.  A Promise is a key card, as it is free, and gives you 2 huge hobbits.  Just remember to keep them from exhaustion.  A Talent for Not Being Seen helps keep the pool down a little, but because it is unique I use only one.  There and Back Again is great, and saves you more than you will realize.  Hobbit Intuition and Stealth are there to help you make it from sites 3 to 6, and after that, when Merry and Pippin are expendable, the keep Sam and Frodo up in size.  PATHS is a game winner vs swarms, and enough of them at site 9 can defeat anything.  Possibly the best card in the deck.<br>
<br>
Shadow -<br>
  If the Ancient Chieftain was not unique, I would run 4.  If I add another Map, I would also add another Balrog, Flame of Udun.  I have lost him using Master Proudfoot, and he is a one man wrecking crew that brings his own friends.  Three Cave Trolls seems to be perfect, and if you can get him down along the Balrog, watch the bodieshimmer the floor.  Backstabbers are underrated, as a runner and backstabber can kill most anyone, except Gandalf and Aragorn.  Runners make it all possible, and are unstoppable vs choke.  Scavengers are great, and nearly free with Armories.  Goblin Scrabblers are good, and when you can kill a Legolas by removing the Tale of Gilgalad, you will learn to swear by them.  Guard Commander is great when you have lots of pool left, and Moria Scouts make elves regret leaving the woods.  Troll&#39;s Keyward and his 3 vitality make him one of the best 3 twilight drops in the game, not to mention his ability.  Cave Troll&#39;s Hammer kills people dead, and scimitars are ungodly good, and with 4 armories, you will find you always have the twilight to do what you want, while deflecting PATHS at site 9.  Goblin Swarms can almost win games on it&#39;s own, but with They Are Coming and Host of Thousands, you always have everything at your disposal.  <br>
<br>
<br>
Gameplay - <br>
Bid 6 safely, and more if need be.  Pippin removes 1, Sam 3, Gaffer heals Sam, Sam removes 1 more, leaving you with 1.  Not much your opponent can do with 1 burden, as Twilight Nazgul needs to spot 2.  Remember you can play Farmer Maggot at site 3 using Merry to draw a card.  Use Master Proudfoot whenever possible, along with They Are Coming.  If you suspect Sleep Caradhras or Secret Sentinals, hold copies of your conditions.  You should be able to run to 9 or swarm your opponent, so be confident in moving if you need, but don&#39;t push too hard.<br>
<br>
D-Mail me with questions, and good luck!<br>
<br>
Scott Poster<br>
